 Baldwin , Count of Flanders. In Flemish and Dutch the letter <i>-t-</i> was generally lost when it occurred between vowels, giving forms such as <i>Ma(h)auld</i>. <i>Maud</i> or <i>Matilda</i> was also the name of the daughter (  1102–67 ) of  Henry I  of England; she was married early in life to the Holy Roman Emperor  Henry V , and later disputed the throne of England with her cousin  Stephen . In  1128  she married  Geoffrey , Count of Anjou. A medieval chronicler commented, ‘she was a good woman, but she had little bliss with him’. The name <i>Maud</i> became quite common in England in the 19th century, when its popularity was influenced in part by  Tennyson's  poem Maud, published in  1855 , but has not been much used since the early decades of the 20th century."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Maud Fauldingworth was born about 1300, in Floore, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of Thomas Fauldingworth. She had at least 1 son with Henry Tilly."},"et":{"Abt 1300–":"umbes 1300–Surnud","1300–Female":"1300–Surnud","1295–1334":"1295–1334","1325–1362":"1325–1362","1275–Male":"1275–Surnud","1325":"1325","Abt 1300":"umbes 1300","1334":"1334","1300":"1300","1275":"1275","Abt 1325":"umbes 1325","1362":"1362","1295":"1295","Flore, Northamptonshire, England":"Flore, Northamptonshire, England","Floore, Northamptonshire, England.":"Floore, Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1300–":"noin 1300–Kuollut","1300–Female":"1300–Kuollut","1295–1334":"1295–1334","1325–1362":"1325–1362","1275–Male":"1275–Kuollut","1325":"1325","Abt 1300":"noin 1300","1334":"1334","1300":"1300","1275":"1275","Abt 1325":"noin 1325","1362":"1362","1295":"1295","Flore, Northamptonshire, England":"Flore, Northamptonshire, England","Floore, Northamptonshire, England.":"Floore, Northamptonshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1300–":"environ 1300–Décédée","1300–Female":"1300–Décédée","1295–1334":"1295–1334","1325–1362":"1325–1362","1275–Male":"127